        dc:description           "Figs 44-56: Lathrobium aspinosum sp. n. (44-51) and L. appendiculatum sp. n. (52-56): habitus (44, 52); forebody (45, 53); male sternite VII (46, 54); male sternite VIII (47, 55); aedeagus in lateral view (48); apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view (49); female sternite VIII (50); female tergites IX-X (51); aedeagus in latero-ventral view (56). Scale bars: 44-45, 52-53: 1.0 mm; 46-51, 54-56: 0.5 mm." ;
